Definition at line 293 of file N_InterPan.h.

void(* N_InterPan_Callback_t::ReceivedInterPanCommand)(uint16_t clusterId, uint16_t payloadLength, uint8_t *pPayload, int8_t rssi, N_Address_Extended_t *pSourceAddress)

Generic callback to handle an Inter-PAN command. Keep this callback last in the list.

Parameters:
clusterIdThe cluster ID that the command was received
payloadLengthThe length of the payload data
pPayloadThe payload data that has been received
rssiThe received signal strength indication
pSourceAddressThe IEEE address of the sender of the of the message
Note:
The payload includes a ZCL header.
This callback is also called for any of the 'known' InterPan commands.
